Ghanaian internet sensation, Firdaus Iddrisu aka Shatta Bandle aka Young Rich Nigga has shared a video announcing his ‘newly acquired’ 2022 Ferrari while trolling Davido. Shatta Bandle, a dwarf in his 20s, is reportedly one of the richest and most influential social media celebrities in Ghana currently. He explained his display of wealth isn’t intended as a show-off but a form of motivation to others. He noted that fact that said being a big boy comes at a price is why he was able to buy a 2022 Ferrari but ‘his boy’, Davido could only afford a 2021 Lamborghini Aventador which served as his Christmas gift to himself last year.   Why I must buy G Wagon with cash payment, by…     Toke Makinwa reveals plans to woo Drake     Easiest way to earn bad name, by Tonto Dikeh   He shared a video which captured the interior and exterior of a white 2022 Ferrari and when he eventually sat on the driver’s seat with another on the passenger’s. While the video played the voice of Shatta Bandle which served as a voice over could explaining what it entails to be a ‘big boy.’ He said: “To be a big boy has a price. I don’t show things I have to push people down. I’m only proving myself to motivate people. “See this my boy OBO, e go buy Lamborghini, and see me, young rich nigga, I go buy Ferrari 2022.” “If you wanna chill with the big boys, follow who know their way.” Bandle captioned the video: “Congratulations to myself I buy this Ferrari 98.000 million US dollars.”